{"lemma":"فِراشِ","slug":"فِراشِ","root":"ف.ر.ش","root_slug":"ف-ر-ش","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-ش","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فِراش","root":"فرش","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33532","n33533","n33536"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B4%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"butterflies","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"moths","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mill wheel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَرَشَ (faraša) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cushion, pillow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blanket, cover"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mattress, bed","examples":[{"text":"أَنْهَضُ مِنَ الْفِرَاشِ","english":"I get up from bed"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"couch"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"carpet layer, carpet spreader"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"servant, attendant, valet"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"office boy, errand boy"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From فَرَشَ (faraša, “to spread, to spread out”); ف ر ش (f r š)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33532","headword_ar":"فَرَاشٌ","root":"fr$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Moths,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, that fly into the flame of a lamp"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flying things"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that fall one after another into the lamp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lighted wick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to burn themselves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [and accord. to modern usage,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"butterflies"},{"kind":"text","text":"also:] a pl., [or rather a coll. gen. n.,] of which the sing. [or n. un.] is ↓ with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) the former mentioned in the Kur ci. 3: (TA:) or the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what one sees, resembling small gnats, falling, one after another, into the fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young locusts, when their wings grow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Mgh, Jel,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and they spread them forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and mount, one upon another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silk-worms;"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. so called because they become like these when they come forth from the cocoon. (Mgh.) It is said in a prov., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToya$u mino faraA$apK","text_ar":"اَطْيَشُ مِنْ فَرَاشَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsteady,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light-witted, than a moth that flies into the flame of the lamp"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$apN","text_ar":"فَرَاشَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2371},{"kind":"text","text":"to signify (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man who is light"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in head;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light-witted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsteady;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) such being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frA$p","text_ar":"فراشة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the lamp, in respect of lightness, or unsteadiness, and contemptibleness. (A, * TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thin pieces of bone, such as fly off from any bone when it is struck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any crusts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coverings, that are upon bone, exclusive of the flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bone of the eyebrow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is thin, of the bone of the head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bones that come forth from the head of a man when it is broken:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$u Alr~aA^osi","text_ar":"فَرَاشُ الرَّاْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain thin bones that are next to the bone that covers the brain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$apN","text_ar":"فَرَاشَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any thin bone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aA^osi","text_ar":"الرَّاْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$apu","text_ar":"فَرَاشَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thin bones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pieces of bone, of the head, such as fly off in consequence of a blow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$u AlZ~ahori","text_ar":"فَرَاشُ الظَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place where the upper parts of the ribs are infixed in"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the spine of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaraA$aAni","text_ar":"الفَرَاشَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two extremities of the haunches, in"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuqorap","text_ar":"نُقْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The parts of the upper portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuwE","text_ar":"فُرُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the two shoulder-blades that rise towards the base of the neck and the even part of the back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, O.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two veins, green,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a dark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ashy, dust-colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaraAni","text_ar":"اَخْضَرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath the tongue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, O, K. * [In the last of these, this signification and the next are erroneously assigned to the sing. word. See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfiraA$u","text_ar":"الفِرَاشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b6-  Also, (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$aA All~ijaAmi","text_ar":"فَرَاشَا اللِّجَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, O,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$ataAhu","text_ar":"فَرَاشَتَاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd in his Book on the Saddle and Bridle,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two iron things with which are made fast the check-straps of the headstall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, O, K.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$N","text_ar":"فَرَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$apN","text_ar":"فَرَاشَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signify The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edge"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything. (Aboo-Sa'eed, in TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nsr","text_ar":"نسر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A3-  And The former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mud that has dried, after the water, upon the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b2-  And it is said to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A little water in pools left by torrents:"},{"kind":"text","text":"n. un. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$apN","text_ar":"فَرَاشَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Little"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bubbles"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habab","text_ar":"حَبَب"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the surface"},{"kind":"text","text":"of [the beverage called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*","text_ar":"نَبِيذ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) and likewise of the water of sweat: (S, * L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little sweat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says IAar. (L.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$u qufolK","text_ar":"فَرَاشُ قُفْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaA$ib","text_ar":"مَنَاشِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"catches"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a lock;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the little pins which fall into corresponding holes in the bolt of the Arabian wooden lock of a door,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which see figured and described in the Introduction to my work on the Modern Egyptians,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is pushed into the hole or staple of the door-post, preventing its being drawn back until they are raised by the key, which has small pins, made to correspond with the holes, so that, being introduced into these, they push up the catching pins:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] n. un. ↓ with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A 'Obeyd, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qufolK","text_ar":"قُفْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA$apu","text_ar":"فَرَاشَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what catches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sticks fast, in a lock;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) [or, as expl. in the Arabic Dictionary of Farhát,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what enters into a lock and makes it fast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its teeth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK;) [which are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the little pins described above:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the word is thought by IDrd to be not Arabic: or, thus applied, it is from the same word as signifying “ a thin bone, ” because of the thinness of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frA$p","text_ar":"فراشة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the lock. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","K","Zj","Fr","Mgh","Jel","A","O"]},{"entry_id":"n33533","headword_ar":"فِرَاشٌ","root":"fr$","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that is spread"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that is spread for one to sit or lie upon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which sense it is used in the Kur ii. 20: (TA:) and particularly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bed, upon which one sleeps:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, Mgh:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afori$apN","text_ar":"اَفْرِشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furu$N","text_ar":"فُرُشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) for which one may say, in the dial. of the Benoo-Temeem,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furo$N","text_ar":"فُرْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sb.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faro$N","text_ar":"فَرْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see what is quoted below from a trad.] ―         -b2-  Hence, (TA,) (tropical:)  A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, S, O, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaArN","text_ar":"اـِزَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liHaAfN","text_ar":"لِحَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furu$N","text_ar":"فُرُشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so used, accord. to some, in the Kur lvi. 33. (K.) ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)  A woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, Er-Rághib:) and a female slave's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"owner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) So, accord. to some, in the words of a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwaladu","text_ar":"الوَلَدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lilofiraA$i walilEaAhiri AlHajaru","text_ar":"لِلْفِرَاشِ وَلِلعَاهِرِ الحَجَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The child is for the husband;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the master of the bed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"who is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the husband,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the owner of the woman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the bed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that there is no ellipsis; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and for the adulterer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fornicator, shall be stones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as you say he shall have dust, meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nothing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., he shall have no right of relationship; or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stoning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAhirN","text_ar":"عَاهِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nest of a bird."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, * TA.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfiraA$u","text_ar":"الفِرَاشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place against which the tongue goes in the furthest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"innermost, part of the mouth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, O, K, TA;) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the lower part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hanak","text_ar":"حَنَك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which word app. here, as it often does, means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firaA$u All~isaAni","text_ar":"فِرَاشُ اللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the portion of skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljilodapu","text_ar":"الجِلْدَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to which is here added"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~an~aA='","text_ar":"الشَّنَّا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", app. a mistranscription which I am unable to rectify,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that covers the bases of the upper teeth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [In the TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaArapu","text_ar":"مَحَارَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hwr","text_ar":"حور"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v., q. v., it is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfiraA$apu","text_ar":"الفِرَاشَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","K","TA","AA","S","O"]},{"entry_id":"n33536","headword_ar":"فَرَّاشٌ","root":"fr$","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who spreads the carpets and similar furniture"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as beds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mattresses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, and keeps them in order:"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. a post-classical word: fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (KL.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}